The paper deals with image registration using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses reducing the spatial information provided to the discriminator, which falls under information theory (cs.IT). The use of GANs for image synthesis and registration also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
